Reasoning: The paper discusses the design of error-correction codes for wireless communication applications, specifically for the block-fading channel model. This falls under the information theory (cs.IT) and networking and internet architecture (cs.NI) sub-categories. The paper also mentions the use of low-density parity-check (LDPC) codes, which are commonly used in coding and cryptography (cs.CC) and multimedia (cs.MM) applications. Additionally, the paper discusses the performance of the codes in various scenarios, which could be considered under the social and information networks (cs.SI) sub-category.
